	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I can confirm what Tokumaru says, I don't think there's anything that really prepares you for assembly other than learning other languages first.  Once you have a basic understanding of loops, if/thens, structures etc. you will have an easier time reconstructing these actions on a more basic level.
<br />
<br />College teaches either beginner stuff you can find on Google, or the forms and database management of typical business apps.
<br />
<br />Video game schools teach things like collision detection and the advanced structures needed for complex games, but nowadays I would expect them to mostly be based around modern languages and 3D engines.
<br />
<br />For assembly, your best bet is forums like this one!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


