		<td><b>a possible roundabout self-teaching solution</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A great book that will teach you the fundamentals of assembly language programming in the clearest, most down to earth way imaginable is Jeff Duntemann's Assembly Language: Step by Step. This teaches x86 assembly; so this would be a roundabout way of learning another processor like 6502. But, it is the background I came from and I can easily say that what I learned from that book made it very easy to learn 6502.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


