	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My opinion would be that none of them will help you in what you're looking for:  both of them will teach you <strong>how</strong> to learn about what you want to do by showing you the basics but it will not teach you what you may want to do.
<br />
<br />Basically, once you've learned enough from school, the rest lies in your hand and your own determination. No school will help you on that. So if your goal is just to do it as a hobby then you can learn it by yourself actually, a school is not necessary.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
